    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-01-29T01:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-01-29T01:25:00-05:00" n="45"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84116/49: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-01-29T09:00:00+02:35"
                            >January 29, 1936—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>54. Communiqué last night reports that on January 21st three Italian planes
                    dropped large quantities mustard gas bombs northeast of Makale. Northwest of
                    Makale Italians are still trying to retake position they lost and heavy
                    artillery bombardments audible day and night since January 23rd.</p>
                <p>Communiqué also refers to minor successes gained by small detachments of Ras
                    Seyum’s army between January 14th and 19th.</p>
                <p>Netherlands Red Cross unit arrived Dessie yesterday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
